  "text": "## Grafana Datasource Plugin Query to Data Frame Chain\n\nThe query flow from HTTP API handler to data frame response follows this path:\n\n### 1. HTTP API Handler (Entry Point)\n**File**: `pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go`\n**Symbol**: `QueryDataHandler()`\n\nThis is the HTTP endpoint handler that receives datasource plugin queries. It:\n- Receives JSON request body and parses it into `data.QueryDataRequest`\n- Extracts datasource UID from URL path parameter\n- Gets the plugin context for the datasource\n- Calls the PluginClient's QueryData method with the request\n- Serializes the response back to JSON using the Responder utility\n\n### 2. Plugin Handler Setup\n**File**: `pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/handler.go`\n**Symbols**: `PluginHandler`, `PluginClient` interface\n\nThe PluginHandler:\n- Implements `http.Handler` interface and routes requests to the appropriate handler\n- Registers the QueryDataHandler at route `/apis/{group}/{version}/namespaces/{namespace}/datasources/{uid}/query`\n- Holds a reference to the PluginClient interface which abstracts the actual plugin implementation\n- PluginClient interface extends `backend.QueryDataHandler` and `backend.AdmissionHandler`\n\n### 3. Plugin Manager Client\n**File**: `pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go`\n**Symbol**: `Service.QueryData()`\n\nThe plugin manager's client service:\n- Gets the Plugin instance from the plugin registry by pluginID and version\n- Calls the plugin's QueryData method\n- Post-processes the response by setting RefID on frames based on response RefID mapping\n- Handles various error types (cancellation, unavailability, request failure)\n\n### 4. Plugin Wrapper\n**File**: `pkg/plugins/plugins.go`\n**Symbol**: `Plugin.QueryData()`\n\nThe Plugin wrapper:\n- Gets the pluginClient from either gRPC implementation or core plugin wrapper\n- Delegates to `pluginClient.QueryData(ctx, req)` where pluginClient implements `backend.QueryDataHandler`\n- Routes to either gRPC remote plugin or local core plugin\n\n### 5. Backend Query Execution\nFor **gRPC plugins**, the chain continues to:\n\n**File**: `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go`\n**Symbol**: `ClientV2.QueryData()`\n\nThe ClientV2 wrapper:\n- Converts `backend.QueryDataRequest` to protobuf format using `backend.ToProto().QueryDataRequest(req)`\n- Calls the gRPC DataClient service method: `c.DataClient.QueryData(ctx, protoReq)`\n- Receives protobuf response and converts back using `backend.FromProto().QueryDataResponse(protoResp)`\n- Handles gRPC status errors appropriately\n\n**File**: `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_proto.go`\n**Symbol**: `protoClient.QueryData()`\n\nThe protoClient:\n- Obtains the gRPC ClientV2 from the plugin\n- Calls `c.DataClient.QueryData(ctx, in, opts...)` where DataClient is the pluginv2.DataClient gRPC stub\n- Returns the protobuf QueryDataResponse\n\nFor **core plugins**, the chain goes to:\n\n**File**: `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/core_plugin.go`\n**Symbol**: `corePlugin.QueryData()`\n\nThe core plugin wrapper:\n- Directly calls the QueryDataHandler if present (e.g., `tempo.Service.QueryData()`, `prometheus.Service.QueryData()`, etc.)\n- Wraps the context with Grafana configuration\n- Returns the backend.QueryDataResponse directly\n\n### 6. Data Frame Serialization\n**File**: `pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go`\n**Symbol**: `QueryDataResponse`\n\nThe QueryDataResponse type:\n- Wraps `backend.QueryDataResponse` with Kubernetes TypeMeta for API server compatibility\n- Contains a `Responses` map keyed by RefID pointing to `backend.DataResponse` objects\n- Each `backend.DataResponse` contains `Frames` (array of `*data.Frame` objects)\n- The Frames contain the actual columnar data with fields, values, and metadata\n\n**File**: `pkg/aggregator/apiserver/util/responder.go`\n**Symbol**: `Responder.Object()`\n\nThe Responder utility:\n- Calls `responsewriters.WriteRawJSON(statusCode, obj, ResponseWriter)` from Kubernetes apiserver\n- This serializes the QueryDataResponse (which is a runtime.Object) to JSON format\n- The backend.QueryDataResponse.Responses map and contained Frames are serialized according to their JSON tags\n- The data frames are marshaled as JSON arrays of columnar values with field metadata\n\n### Summary of Key Components\n\n1. **Entry**: HTTP handler receives JSON request at `/apis/*/datasources/{uid}/query`\n2. **Routing**: PluginHandler routes to QueryDataHandler which validates and calls PluginClient\n3. **Plugin Management**: Plugin manager looks up the appropriate plugin implementation (gRPC or core)\n4. **Plugin Invocation**: Plugin wrapper delegates to the actual plugin's QueryData handler\n5. **Backend Execution**: Plugin executes the query and returns backend.QueryDataResponse with data frames\n6. **Serialization**: QueryDataResponse is wrapped with Kubernetes TypeMeta and serialized to JSON via Responder\n7. **Output**: HTTP response contains JSON representation of the data frames with all field metadata\n\nThe entire flow uses the Grafana Plugin SDK's type system (`backend.*` types) and gRPC protocol (pluginv2 protobuf types) for cross-process communication with remote plugins, while core plugins operate directly with the backend types."
}

